00:53.531 --> 00:55.968
♪ I'LL BE READY

00:57.231 --> 00:58.971
♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS

00:59.842 --> 01:01.931
♪ I'M ALWAYS HERE

01:20.993 --> 01:22.647
♪ 'CAUSE I'M ALWAYS READY

01:22.778 --> 01:25.998
♪ I WON'T LET YOU
OUT OF MY SIGHT ♪

01:28.088 --> 01:29.001
♪ NO

01:29.132 --> 01:31.830
♪ I'LL BE READY

01:31.961 --> 01:32.962
♪ I'LL BE READY

01:33.093 --> 01:35.486
♪ NEVER YOU FEAR

01:35.617 --> 01:36.966
♪ NO, DON'T YOU FEAR

01:37.097 --> 01:40.970
♪ I'LL BE READY

01:41.101 --> 01:43.233
♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS

01:44.060 --> 01:46.628
♪ I'M ALWAYS HERE.

02:01.425 --> 02:05.821
[RHYTHMIC MUSIC]

02:16.310 --> 02:17.963
-CHECK, CLUE NUMBER ONE.

02:18.094 --> 02:19.574
IF YOU'RE GOING TO FIND
ME YOU'RE GOING TO HAVE TO

02:19.704 --> 02:21.097
THINK LIKE A NEANDERTHAL.

02:21.228 --> 02:22.490
-LIKE A WHAT?

02:22.620 --> 02:25.145
-A NEANDERTHAL,
YOU DUMMY! A CAVEMAN!

02:44.512 --> 02:46.992
-ZACK, TELL ME YOU'RE
NOT IN THE CAVE.

02:47.123 --> 02:48.733
-COME ON IN HERE, IT'S AWESOME!

02:48.864 --> 02:51.171
-TELL ZACK TO GET OUT OF
THERE, THE WAVES ARE HUGE!

02:51.301 --> 02:52.476
-ZACK, THE WAVES
ARE REALLY BIG.

02:52.607 --> 02:54.522
YOU BETTER GET OUT, NOW!

03:04.619 --> 03:05.794
[CAR HORN HONKING]

03:10.799 --> 03:11.713
-CODY: HEY, BABY!

03:11.843 --> 03:13.193
-HI, HOW WAS YOUR DAY?

03:13.323 --> 03:14.846
-CODY: PERFECT NOW
THAT YOU'RE HERE.

03:20.112 --> 03:21.244
-ALL SYSTEMS ARE GO.

03:21.810 --> 03:22.811
-NO KIDDING, EVERYTHING?

03:22.941 --> 03:24.987
-YEP, EVERY LAST DETAIL.

03:25.117 --> 03:26.684
-AW, CJ, YOU ARE THE BEST!

03:26.815 --> 03:28.382
I'VE BEEN LOOKING FORWARD
TO THIS ALL DAY LONG.

03:28.512 --> 03:30.775
-I HAVE YOUR FAVORITE
WINE, YOUR FAVORITE MUSIC,

03:30.906 --> 03:31.994
YOUR FAVORITE FOOD.

03:32.908 --> 03:34.170
WHAT ELSE COULD A MAN ASK FOR?

03:35.476 --> 03:36.955
[LAUGHS]

03:37.086 --> 03:38.522
I'M GOING TO MAKE ALL
YOUR WISHES COME TRUE.

03:40.524 --> 03:42.700
-LET'S START RIGHT
NOW WITH MY FIRST WISH.

03:42.831 --> 03:44.398
-WHAT'S THAT?

03:44.528 --> 03:45.921
-HELP ME CLOSE THE TOWER
SO WE CAN GET OUT OF HERE.

03:46.051 --> 03:46.574
-YEAH.

03:46.704 --> 03:47.270
[LAUGHS]

03:49.098 --> 03:50.012
[GASPS]

03:50.142 --> 03:54.582
[TENSE MUSIC]

03:54.712 --> 03:56.671
-HELP! HELP ME!

03:57.628 --> 03:59.326
HELP!

03:59.456 --> 04:00.936
-GO GET HELP! REMEMBER THE
LIFEGUARD TOWER WE PASSED?

04:01.893 --> 04:02.894
ZACK?

04:04.200 --> 04:05.245
-HELP!

04:06.333 --> 04:08.378
-SO, ARE YOU HUNGRY?

04:09.423 --> 04:12.382
-LET'S JUST SAY MY
APPETITE IS VORACIOUS.

04:17.474 --> 04:18.301
[LAUGHS]

04:19.433 --> 04:20.390
-CJ: CATCH!

04:23.828 --> 04:25.613
-JUST TELL ME, TELL ME
WHAT THE SURPRISE IS!

04:25.743 --> 04:26.614
-NO, I'M NOT
TELLING YOU ANYTHING.

04:26.744 --> 04:27.919
-COME ON, CJ!

04:28.050 --> 04:29.181
-IT'D BE BETTER
IF YOU DON'T KNOW.

04:29.312 --> 04:30.922
OH, IT'S HOT OUT.
-IT'S NOT FAIR!

04:31.053 --> 04:32.489
-YO, LIFEGUARD!

04:34.099 --> 04:35.144
[PANTING]

04:35.275 --> 04:36.841
MY BROTHER AND I
WERE PLAYING

04:36.972 --> 04:38.495
HIDE-AND-GO-SEEK
ON OUR WALKIE-TALKIES,

04:38.626 --> 04:39.801
AND HE'S STUCK IN
THE CAVE DOWN THERE.

04:39.931 --> 04:41.193
-CAN YOU TAKE US TO HIM?
-YEAH.

04:41.324 --> 04:42.020
-LET'S GO!

04:42.151 --> 04:44.893
[TENSE MUSIC]

04:49.811 --> 04:50.768
-HELP!

04:58.385 --> 05:00.865
-MY BROTHER ZACK, HE'S
TRAPPED IN THE CAVE!

05:02.214 --> 05:03.912
[GRUNTS]

05:10.527 --> 05:13.400
-ZACK: HELP ME, I'M IN HERE!

05:14.749 --> 05:16.838
[GASPS] HELP ME! HELP!

05:17.491 --> 05:18.405
I'M HERE!

05:19.406 --> 05:23.410
HELP, HELP!
HELP ME! I'M IN HERE!

05:24.411 --> 05:26.674
PLEASE HELP! HELP ME!

05:33.768 --> 05:35.987
OVER HERE! HELP!

05:40.601 --> 05:42.777
-ALL RIGHT, I GOT
YOU! I GOT YOU.

05:43.647 --> 05:45.954
ALL RIGHT NOW WE'RE GOING
TO TAKE A LITTLE SWIM, OKAY?

05:46.650 --> 05:48.652
CAN YOU TAKE A DEEP
BREATH AND HOLD IT FOR ME?

05:48.783 --> 05:49.740
ALL RIGHT.

05:50.611 --> 05:53.831
ONE, TWO, BIG BREATH, THREE!

05:53.962 --> 05:54.876
[GASPS]

05:55.529 --> 05:57.618
-DON'T WORRY GUYS,
HE'S GOING TO FIND HIM.

05:58.662 --> 06:00.229
[GASPING]

06:03.841 --> 06:05.495
GRAB THE CAN!
-OKAY.

06:08.498 --> 06:09.717
[GRUNTING]

06:13.024 --> 06:14.112
-THERE!

06:19.030 --> 06:20.292
OKAY, I'VE GOT HIM.

06:34.524 --> 06:36.047
-ALL RIGHT, YOU'RE GOING
TO BE ALL RIGHT, BUDDY.

06:36.657 --> 06:37.919
-THANKS FOR SAVING ME.

06:38.049 --> 06:39.529
-COULD'VE GOTTEN
YOURSELF KILLED, BOZO.

06:39.660 --> 06:41.488
-DOESN'T MATTER,
I'M DEAD ANYWAY.

06:41.618 --> 06:42.793
LOST DAD'S WALKIE-TALKIE.

06:43.446 --> 06:44.665
-OKAY GUYS, BACK
TO HEADQUARTERS.

06:44.795 --> 06:45.840
I'M GOING
TO CALL YOUR PARENTS.

06:45.970 --> 06:46.841
-GET WALKING.

06:47.885 --> 06:50.758
[BIG BAND MUSIC]

06:52.455 --> 06:56.198
♪ TIME IS LIKE A STORY
THAT WE'VE NOT READ BEFORE ♪

06:56.328 --> 06:58.374
[CHEERING]

07:01.682 --> 07:03.901
♪ NOW IS THE TIME
TO TAKE A CHANCE ♪

07:04.032 --> 07:06.208
♪ GIVE IT YOUR ALL ONCE MORE

07:06.338 --> 07:08.471
♪ OVER THE RULES I DOUBLE TOP

07:08.602 --> 07:10.430
♪ HIT AT CENTER STAGE...

07:13.955 --> 07:15.173
-WHERE IS SHE?

07:15.304 --> 07:16.218
WHERE IS SHE?

07:16.348 --> 07:17.393
-SORRY, MR. BLANTON.

07:18.133 --> 07:19.308
SHE'S USUALLY ON TIME.

07:19.439 --> 07:20.788
-YEAH, WELL THIS
IS THE LAST TIME

07:20.918 --> 07:21.832
I'M GOING TO GIVE
THAT WOMAN ANYTHING.

07:22.616 --> 07:23.921
-DEALER: PLACE YOUR BET.

07:24.748 --> 07:25.706
-THERE SHE IS.

07:26.446 --> 07:28.230
-HEY, SHELLEY!

07:28.360 --> 07:30.711
WHERE YOU BEEN? COME ON!

07:30.841 --> 07:32.539
YOU'RE MY GOOD LUCK CHARM!

07:32.669 --> 07:34.584
YOU KNOW I CAN'T
WIN WITHOUT YOU.

07:34.715 --> 07:35.933
-HI, TONY!

07:36.543 --> 07:37.935
-MY GOOD LUCK CHARM!

07:38.066 --> 07:39.546
-DO YOU LIKE MY DRESS?
-YEAH, BEAUTIFUL.

07:39.676 --> 07:40.851
-YEAH?

07:40.982 --> 07:42.026
-JUST BEAUTIFUL.
OKAY, HERE WE ARE.

07:42.157 --> 07:43.332
LET'S DO IT!
-HERE WE GO.

07:43.463 --> 07:44.681
-I NEED YOU TO WIN BIG FOR ME,

07:44.812 --> 07:46.291
LIKE THE MONTE CARLO
LAST SUMMER.

07:46.422 --> 07:47.989
-ALL RIGHT.
-ALL RIGHT, COVER THE LINE.

07:48.119 --> 07:49.599
-BUT TONY,
THOSE ARE THOUSANDS!

07:49.730 --> 07:51.471
-THAT'S ALL RIGHT,
I GOT MY GOOD LUCK CHARM!

07:51.601 --> 07:52.907
-[LAUGHS] OKAY.

07:53.037 --> 07:54.430
PUT A QUARTER EACH
ON THE HARD ROLLS.

07:54.561 --> 07:55.779
HERE WE GO, YOU OKAY?

07:55.910 --> 07:56.737
-I'M OKAY.

07:57.738 --> 07:59.000
[LAUGHTER]

07:59.130 --> 08:00.175
ALL RIGHT, COME ON.

08:00.305 --> 08:01.611
-HERE WE GO.

08:01.742 --> 08:03.004
YES!

08:03.134 --> 08:04.396
-SHE ROLLS A 3. CRAPS.
[MURMURING]

08:08.749 --> 08:09.967
I'M SORRY TONY, I--

08:10.098 --> 08:10.968
-SHUT UP, SHUT
UP AND ROLL AGAIN.

08:12.361 --> 08:14.058
PUT THE WHOLE QUARTER OF
A MILLION CREDIT LINE--

08:14.189 --> 08:16.191
HEY! LISTEN TO ME.

08:16.321 --> 08:17.714
I'M GOING TO BET THE WHOLE

08:17.845 --> 08:19.107
QUARTER OF A MILLION
DOLLAR CREDIT LINE,

08:19.237 --> 08:21.588
COVER ALL NUMBERS. YOU GOT IT?

08:23.328 --> 08:24.373
-YES SIR, RIGHT
ON THE FRONT LINE.

08:24.504 --> 08:25.896
-ALL RIGHT, DO IT.

08:26.027 --> 08:27.637
-OKAY.
-ALL RIGHT.

08:28.812 --> 08:30.205
-QUARTER OF A MILLION DOLLARS?

08:30.335 --> 08:31.554
-COME ON, IT'S ALL
RIGHT, IT'S ALL RIGHT.

08:31.685 --> 08:33.513
COME ON, DON'T THINK,
DO IT. COME ON.

08:33.643 --> 08:34.948
-OKAY!

08:35.078 --> 08:36.037
-COME ON, COME ON,
COME ON, COME ON.

08:36.167 --> 08:37.559
-ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT.

08:37.691 --> 08:39.039
WE GOT IT WORKING.

08:39.169 --> 08:40.171
-AH, COME ON!

08:40.302 --> 08:41.738
-HERE WE GO, HUH? GREAT!

08:41.869 --> 08:43.434
-YES, YES!

08:43.566 --> 08:45.873
-CRAPS AGAIN, LADY LOSES.

08:48.528 --> 08:49.616
-DAMN IT!
[THUDDING]

08:51.269 --> 08:52.836
-TONY, I--

08:52.967 --> 08:55.404
-TAKE YOUR BAD LUCK
AND GET AS FAR AWAY

08:55.535 --> 08:56.536
FROM ME AS POSSIBLE.

08:56.666 --> 08:58.189
YOU HEAR ME? YOU HEAR ME?

08:58.320 --> 08:59.321
NOW!

08:59.451 --> 09:00.757
-TONY--
-NOW!

09:06.633 --> 09:08.243
-BE CAREFUL, HONEY.

09:08.373 --> 09:10.593
TONY'S LAST TWO GIRLS
WHOSE "GOOD LUCK" WORE OFF,

09:11.333 --> 09:12.769
WERE NEVER SEEN AGAIN.

09:12.900 --> 09:14.989
-WHAT? WHAT?

09:15.119 --> 09:17.992
[SOLEMN MUSIC]

09:18.122 --> 09:21.865
-NOW! I WANT YOU TO
LEAVE NOW! YOU HEAR ME?

09:21.996 --> 09:23.345
GET OUT OF HERE!

09:23.475 --> 09:25.521
TAKE HER UP TO THE
SUITE, I'LL BE UP THERE.

09:28.176 --> 09:29.177
[ELEVATOR DINGS]

09:29.307 --> 09:30.700
-WHAT A NIGHT.

09:30.831 --> 09:32.310
I MEAN SERIOUSLY,
HE DIDN'T HAVE TO BET

09:32.441 --> 09:34.617
ALL OF THE MONEY, YOU KNOW?

09:34.748 --> 09:36.358
I ALMOST HAD A HEART ATTACK.

09:36.488 --> 09:38.360
AND HE DIDN'T HAVE TO
SPEAK TO ME LIKE THAT,

09:38.490 --> 09:40.971
I HAVE NEVER EVER HEARD
HIM TALK TO ME LIKE THAT!

09:41.102 --> 09:43.713
I MEAN, SERIOUSLY, WHAT
IS THE BIG DEAL HERE?

09:43.844 --> 09:45.062
WHAT'S GOING ON?

09:45.193 --> 09:46.368
-MS. SANDS, HAS
ANYONE EVER TOLD YOU

09:46.498 --> 09:48.196
THAT YOU TALK TOO MUCH?

09:54.419 --> 09:55.682
[SIGHS]

09:59.033 --> 10:01.992
LOOK, MS. SANDS,
MR. BLANTON WILL BE UP SOON.

10:02.514 --> 10:04.734
SO DO YOURSELF
A FAVOR, STAY PUT,

10:04.865 --> 10:06.954
AND DON'T GET INTO
ANY MORE TROUBLE.

10:07.781 --> 10:10.522
[QUIRKY MUSIC]

10:14.526 --> 10:15.745
[SIGHS]

10:20.663 --> 10:22.143
-QUARTER MILLION
DOLLAR CREDIT LINE,

10:22.273 --> 10:23.797
HE COULD HAVE GOT
A BETTER SUITE.

10:39.987 --> 10:42.729
YES, YES, YES, YES!

10:47.690 --> 10:48.909
LET'S SEE HERE.

10:50.171 --> 10:51.781
[GASPS] YES!

10:52.564 --> 10:53.783
BINGO!

10:53.914 --> 10:57.308
[COMPUTER BEEPING]

11:05.099 --> 11:05.926
[GASPS]

11:06.666 --> 11:09.843
[SHUFFLING MUSIC]

11:09.973 --> 11:14.238
[GASPS] I'LL BET
THAT WASN'T REPORTED!

11:15.805 --> 11:19.896
[QUIRKY MUSIC]

11:30.777 --> 11:32.082
[ELEVATOR DINGS]

11:34.432 --> 11:37.131
-QUARTER OF A MILLION
DOLLARS, UP IN A PUFF OF SMOKE.

11:37.261 --> 11:40.525
AND THAT WOMAN HAS ALWAYS BEEN
MY LUCKY STREAK!

11:40.656 --> 11:42.397
IT JUST MAKES YOU CRAZY.

11:43.398 --> 11:45.139
IT JUST MAKES ME
CRAZY, I TELL YOU.

11:49.839 --> 11:50.710
[LAUGHS]

11:58.413 --> 11:59.327
-SHELLEY!

12:01.111 --> 12:02.896
[TENSE MUSIC]

12:06.073 --> 12:06.987
VINNIE!

12:11.774 --> 12:13.602
VINNIE SHE GOT THE
DISK, SHE GOT MY FILES.

12:14.124 --> 12:16.083
YOU GOT TO FIND HER, YOU
GOT TO GET THAT DISK BACK.

12:16.213 --> 12:17.911
-I'LL GET THE BOYS ON IT
RIGHT AWAY, MR. BLANTON.

12:22.742 --> 12:26.528
[LANGUID MUSIC]

12:26.658 --> 12:28.051
[KNOCKING]

12:28.182 --> 12:30.445
-MM, WHO COULD THAT BE?
IT'S AFTER MIDNIGHT.

12:30.575 --> 12:34.754
-I DON'T KNOW. WITH ANY LUCK,
WHOEVER IT IS WILL GO AWAY.

12:34.884 --> 12:35.755
-MM.

12:37.539 --> 12:38.409
[KNOCKING]

12:39.019 --> 12:40.281
THEY'RE NOT GOING AWAY.

12:41.195 --> 12:42.805
[QUICK KNOCKING]

12:42.936 --> 12:43.501
-THAT WAS A DESPERATE KNOCK,
I'D BETTER GO GET IT.

12:43.632 --> 12:44.764
-[SIGHS] NO, CJ!

12:49.551 --> 12:50.770
-OKAY, THIS BETTER BE GOOD.

12:52.467 --> 12:54.774
-HI, SWEETHEART!
-MOM!

12:54.904 --> 12:58.603
-OH, MY CASEY JEAN, I'M
SO HAPPY TO SEE YOU!

12:59.213 --> 13:00.301
-CJ: WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

13:00.431 --> 13:01.563
-WELL, I--

13:02.172 --> 13:04.261
OH, YOU'RE BUSY!

13:05.175 --> 13:07.830
I'M INTERRUPTING.
I'LL COME BACK.

13:07.961 --> 13:09.310
-NO, NO, NO,
STAY, STAY, STAY,

13:09.440 --> 13:10.964
WE JUST OPENED A BOTTLE
OF MOET CHAMPAGNE.

13:11.094 --> 13:12.487
-SHELLEY: OH!
-CJ: HOW COME YOU

13:12.617 --> 13:13.227
DIDN'T CALL, I COULD
HAVE PICKED YOU UP.

13:13.880 --> 13:14.794
-WELL...

13:14.924 --> 13:16.143
-SOMETHING'S UP, ISN'T IT?

13:16.273 --> 13:17.797
WHAT'D YOU DO,
WHAT'S GOING ON?

13:17.927 --> 13:19.581
-UH...

13:19.711 --> 13:22.062
I DON'T NEED AN EXCUSE TO
COME AND SEE MY BABY GIRL!

13:22.192 --> 13:23.628
[LAUGHS]

13:23.759 --> 13:25.326
-OR YOU'RE SCARED TO
DEATH OF EARTHQUAKES

13:25.456 --> 13:27.023
AND YOU SWORE YOU'D NEVER
COME BACK TO CALIFORNIA.

13:27.154 --> 13:28.982
QUOTE, "I LOVE TO DANCE
BUT NOT WITH MY FURNITURE."

13:29.112 --> 13:32.420
-[LAUGHS] SILLY BUMPS
AND GRINDS, I'M OVER IT!

13:32.550 --> 13:33.334
-OH, REALLY?

13:33.464 --> 13:35.162
-HI!

13:35.292 --> 13:36.859
-THIS IS CODY. CODY, THIS
IS SHELLEY SANDS, MY MOM.

13:36.990 --> 13:39.079
-NO KIDDING, IT'S UM,
IT'S A PLEASURE TO MEET YOU.

13:39.209 --> 13:42.299
-SHELLEY: HOW DO YOU DO?
-SHELLEY SANDS?

13:42.430 --> 13:44.432
-OH, MY MOM IS THE
BEST DANCER IN VEGAS.

13:44.562 --> 13:46.347
-WELL... [LAUGHS]

13:47.348 --> 13:50.873
I NEEDED A CATCHY STAGE
NAME FOR MY VEGAS SHOW.

13:51.004 --> 13:53.789
AND I JUST HAPPENED TO BE
THERE WITH CASEY JEAN'S DAD

13:53.920 --> 13:56.052
WHEN, WELL, YOU KNOW...

13:56.183 --> 13:57.924
[LAUGHTER]

13:58.054 --> 14:00.013
HEY, SHE TOLD ME YOU
WERE A HANDSOME GUY

14:00.143 --> 14:02.624
BUT SHE DID NOT TELL ME
YOU ARE A HEARTTHROB.

14:03.233 --> 14:04.931
YOU'LL HAVE TO TELL ME
MORE ABOUT YOURSELF, HUH?

14:05.061 --> 14:06.193
-I'D LOVE TO.

14:09.544 --> 14:10.850
-I AM INTERRUPTING.

14:10.980 --> 14:12.677
I CANNOT BARGE IN
ON YOU LIKE THIS.

14:12.808 --> 14:13.548
-CJ: NO!
-SHELLEY: I'M GOING TO GO,

14:13.678 --> 14:15.071
I'LL BE BACK.

14:15.202 --> 14:16.116
-NO! CAROLINE, SHE'S
GONE FOR THE WEEKEND

14:16.246 --> 14:17.030
SO YOU CAN HAVE HER ROOM.

14:17.682 --> 14:19.075
-ARE YOU SURE?

14:19.206 --> 14:20.816
-YEAH, ABSOLUTELY. ALL YOURS.

14:21.773 --> 14:23.645
-WELL, ALL RIGHT. OKAY.

14:23.775 --> 14:24.559
-HERE, LET ME GET THAT.

14:24.689 --> 14:25.908
-NO, NO, NO,

14:26.039 --> 14:27.649
YOU TWO JUST...
-CODY: ARE YOU SURE?

14:27.779 --> 14:29.042
-STAY THERE, STAY THERE,
I'LL HANDLE THIS YOU TWO,

14:29.172 --> 14:31.479
I'LL JUST SAY
GOODNIGHT. NIGHT, NIGHT!

14:38.051 --> 14:40.662
-SO, THAT'S MOM.

14:41.402 --> 14:43.534
-YEP, FASTEN YOUR SEATBELT.

14:45.232 --> 14:46.059
[LAUGHS]

14:48.365 --> 14:49.323
[KNOCKING]

14:49.453 --> 14:50.411
-JIMMY: COME IN!

14:51.368 --> 14:53.414
-OH, JIMMY, IS IT OKAY IF
I BRING MY MOM THROUGH HERE?

14:53.544 --> 14:54.632
SHE WANTS
TO TAKE A LOOK AROUND.

14:54.763 --> 14:55.982
-SURE.
-HI THERE.

14:56.112 --> 14:57.679
-HI.
-THIS IS THE MEN'S LOCKER ROOM.

14:57.809 --> 14:58.985
IT'S WHERE WE ALL CHANGE BEFORE

14:59.115 --> 15:00.551
WE GO OUT TO OUR
TOWER ASSIGNMENTS.

15:01.726 --> 15:03.337
AND THIS IS--
[GASPS]

15:03.467 --> 15:04.512
-JOE: OH!
-OH.

15:04.642 --> 15:07.384
-JOE: UH, SORRY.
-SORRY, JOE.

15:09.169 --> 15:10.822
[LAUGHS]

15:10.953 --> 15:12.824
ANYWAY, THIS IS
THE LADIES' SIDE.

15:12.955 --> 15:13.825
MOM!

15:15.392 --> 15:16.611
THIS IS WHERE A
LOT OF THE GUARDS

15:16.741 --> 15:17.612
WERE TRAPPED DURING
THE EARTHQUAKE.

15:17.742 --> 15:20.745
-OH! OH, OH, YEAH.

15:20.876 --> 15:22.965
HI! I'M CJ'S MOM.

15:23.096 --> 15:24.010
-YEAH!

15:25.098 --> 15:27.448
-HOW DID YOU OVERCOME YOUR
PARANOIA OF EARTHQUAKES ANYWAY?

15:28.666 --> 15:30.538
-HYPNOTISM.
-HYPNOTISM.

15:30.668 --> 15:32.322
-MM-HM.

15:32.453 --> 15:33.367
-I THOUGHT YOU WERE SCARED
TO DEATH TO BE HYPNOTIZED.

15:34.107 --> 15:35.586
-YOU KNOW,
I FIGURED IT WAS TIME

15:35.717 --> 15:37.153
TO GET OVER THAT FEAR TOO.

15:37.284 --> 15:38.676
SO HERE I AM!

15:38.807 --> 15:40.374
I'M SO HAPPY TO
BE WITH YOU, HONEY!

15:40.504 --> 15:42.463
-OH, ME TOO!
-THIS IS GOING TO BE SO FUN.

15:42.593 --> 15:44.204
-YEAH.
OKAY WELL, I HAVE TO GO UPSTAIRS

15:44.334 --> 15:45.509
TO GET MY TOWER ASSIGNMENT.

15:46.032 --> 15:47.381
-SHELLEY: OKAY.
-CJ: ARE YOU READY?

15:47.511 --> 15:48.948
-YOU KNOW WHAT, I'LL
BE ALONG IN A LITTLE BIT

15:49.078 --> 15:51.298
BECAUSE I WANT TO PUT ON
LOTS OF SUNSCREEN, OKAY?

15:51.428 --> 15:52.429
-OKAY. YOU GUYS COMING?

15:53.126 --> 15:55.302
-I WON'T TAKE LONG, I PROMISE.
-OKAY!

16:05.486 --> 16:09.707
[QUIRKY MUSIC]

16:20.457 --> 16:25.288
[LANGUID MUSIC]

16:43.393 --> 16:45.526
-HEY, MOM!
-HI, HONEY!

16:45.656 --> 16:47.745
OH, WHAT A WAY TO WORK!

16:47.876 --> 16:49.747
-I KNOW, THIS IS MY
OFFICE. ISN'T IT GREAT?

16:49.878 --> 16:51.662
-IT'S BEAUTIFUL!

16:54.404 --> 16:55.797
-HEY, HOW'S IT GOING?

16:56.972 --> 16:57.494
-WOW!

16:58.887 --> 17:00.628
[LAUGHS] CASEY JEAN,

17:00.758 --> 17:02.673
YOU DID NOT TELL
ME ABOUT ALL THESE

17:02.804 --> 17:04.806
HANDSOME HUNKS YOU
HAVE IN YOUR LIFE.

17:04.935 --> 17:06.373
HI.
-HI.

17:06.502 --> 17:08.288
-I'M SHELLEY SANDS,
I'M CASEY JEAN'S MOM.

17:08.417 --> 17:10.377
YOU MIGHT BE?
-THAT'S MY BOSS, MOM.

17:10.507 --> 17:12.031
-MITCH, MITCH BUCHANNON.

17:12.161 --> 17:14.032
YOUR MOM?
-YEAH.

17:14.163 --> 17:16.339
-SHELLEY: YOUR BOSS, OH WOW!
-BOY: WHOA!

17:18.037 --> 17:22.737
[OMINOUS MUSIC]

17:46.282 --> 17:48.415
-NOW IF HE'S YOUR
BOSS, WHY DON'T YOU JUST

17:48.545 --> 17:50.634
COME TO DINNER TONIGHT BECAUSE
I'M GOING TO BE COOKING.

17:50.765 --> 17:52.027
-HELP!

17:52.158 --> 17:52.984
-AND WE CAN GET
TO KNOW EACH OTHER.

17:53.115 --> 17:53.898
-EXCUSE ME. COME ON!

17:54.943 --> 17:55.944
-BOY: HELP!

17:58.425 --> 17:59.382
HELP!

18:01.906 --> 18:06.694
[CROWD MURMURING]

18:18.880 --> 18:20.969
-MITCH: OKAY, OKAY,
I GOT YOU, I GOT YOU.

18:28.672 --> 18:31.545
-WOMAN: WHAT HAPPENED?
I DIDN'T SEE ANYTHING!

18:31.675 --> 18:33.373
-MITCH: OKAY, TAKE IT EASY.
-CJ: GRAB THE CAN.

18:33.503 --> 18:34.635
-MITCH: WE'LL SWIM YOU IN.
-CJ: IT'S GOING TO BE OKAY.

18:34.765 --> 18:35.984
-MITCH: ATTA BOY.
-IT'S OKAY.

18:36.115 --> 18:37.333
-WOMAN: LOOKS
LIKE THEY GOT HIM!

18:41.946 --> 18:44.253
-VINNIE! HOW DID YOU FIND ME?

18:44.384 --> 18:45.646
-YOU WERE ALWAYS BRAGGING ABOUT

18:45.776 --> 18:46.821
YOUR DAUGHTER THE LIFEGUARD.

18:47.778 --> 18:48.997
TONY'S AT THE RITZ-CARLTON,

18:49.128 --> 18:51.260
AND HE'D LIKE TO SEE YOU. NOW.

18:51.391 --> 18:53.871
-YEAH, WELL, I DON'T
WANT TO SEE HIM, EVER!

18:54.437 --> 18:56.526
-THAT'S FUNNY, THAT'S
WHAT HE SAID YOU'D SAY.

18:56.657 --> 18:57.614
NOW LET'S GO!

18:58.485 --> 18:59.747
-OW!

18:59.877 --> 19:03.229
HEY!
HEY, LET GO OF ME!

19:03.359 --> 19:05.622
YOU DON'T HAVE TO
DRAG ME THE WHOLE WAY!

19:06.275 --> 19:07.363
HEY LISTEN VINNIE,
WHY DON'T YOU JUST

19:07.494 --> 19:09.148
GET A REGULAR JOB, WILL YOU?

19:10.192 --> 19:11.106
-HANG IN THERE!

19:11.237 --> 19:13.064
-OH, GOD, THAT'S MY BOY!

19:14.283 --> 19:15.110
[COUGHING]

19:15.241 --> 19:17.765
ZACK! ZACK!

19:17.895 --> 19:19.288
-YOU HIS MOTHER?
-YEAH.

19:19.419 --> 19:20.637
-OKAY. HE'S ALL RIGHT.

19:20.768 --> 19:22.117
HE JUST SUCKED UP
HALF THE OCEAN.

19:22.248 --> 19:23.249
[LAUGHTER]

19:24.424 --> 19:25.686
-HEY!

19:26.904 --> 19:28.645
-LISTEN, YOU JUST LET GO OF ME,

19:28.776 --> 19:30.647
YOU BIG BOSS!

19:30.778 --> 19:33.128
YOU OVERGROWN JABRONI!
-CJ: HEY!

19:33.259 --> 19:34.260
[GRUNTING]

19:35.739 --> 19:36.697
-HUH!

19:39.656 --> 19:42.616
-WHO WAS THAT?
-NOBODY.

19:44.095 --> 19:45.314
-WANT ME TO GO AFTER HIM?

19:45.445 --> 19:47.664
-NAH, HE DIDN'T DO ANYTHING.

19:47.795 --> 19:49.449
-I SAW YOU STRUGGLING
WITH HIM, MOM.

19:49.579 --> 19:51.755
-NO, NO, IT WAS NOTHING.

19:51.886 --> 19:53.235
IT WAS THE SILLIEST THING.

19:53.366 --> 19:54.932
WE BOTH FOUND A
HUNDRED DOLLAR BILL

19:55.063 --> 19:57.283
IN THE SAND AND THAT'S
ALL THERE WAS TO IT.

20:00.155 --> 20:01.069
NO, SERIOUSLY.

20:01.896 --> 20:04.594
IT WAS $100, HE WANTED
IT, I WANTED IT.

20:04.725 --> 20:06.683
AND THAT'S ALL
THERE WAS TO IT SO,

20:06.814 --> 20:09.208
LET'S NOT MAKE A BIG
DEAL OUT OF THIS.

20:09.338 --> 20:11.645
LET'S JUST GO AND
ENJOY THE DAY, OKAY?

20:12.254 --> 20:13.342
COME ON, HONEY.

20:13.473 --> 20:14.430
-YOUR MOM, HUH?

20:15.518 --> 20:16.737
HOW COME YOU NEVER
TOLD ME ABOUT HER?

20:17.433 --> 20:18.347
-MAKE SENSE NOW?

20:22.917 --> 20:27.356
[QUIRKY MUSIC]
[TAPPING]

20:31.055 --> 20:32.405
-SOMETHING WRONG?

20:34.276 --> 20:36.670
-I FEEL LIKE A SINGLE
PARENT WITH TWO CHILDREN,

20:36.800 --> 20:39.325
EXCEPT FOR ONE'S MY MOTHER
AND THE OTHER'S MY BOYFRIEND.

20:40.151 --> 20:42.110
I DON'T KNOW WHO TO
WORRY ABOUT FIRST.

20:42.806 --> 20:44.155
[KNOCKING]

20:47.942 --> 20:49.770
-AH, MAYBE I CAN HELP.

20:49.900 --> 20:50.988
-OH, REALLY?

20:51.119 --> 20:52.860
-YOUR MOTHER IS
HEADED THIS WAY.

20:52.990 --> 20:55.123
-LISTEN, YOU DO A GREAT JOB!

20:55.254 --> 20:56.777
-THANKS!

20:56.907 --> 20:58.648
-HAVEN'T SEEN ONE OF THOSE
IN A LONG TIME! [LAUGHS]

20:59.388 --> 21:00.607
HI, HONEY!

21:02.304 --> 21:03.653
I'M CJ'S MOM.
HAPPY TO MEET YOU.

21:04.524 --> 21:05.612
HI, HI!

21:05.742 --> 21:06.961
-CJ: HI.
-MITCH: HEY!

21:07.091 --> 21:08.789
-HI. OKAY, I'M
EXPECTING BOTH OF YOU

21:08.919 --> 21:10.312
FOR DINNER TONIGHT.

21:10.443 --> 21:11.922
I'M GOING TO GO RUN
SOME ERRANDS, ALL RIGHT?

21:12.053 --> 21:13.402
-OH, WHOA, WHOA,
WHOA, WHAT ERRANDS?

21:14.142 --> 21:15.883
-I HAVE TO GET SOME
THINGS FOR DINNER

21:16.013 --> 21:19.408
BECAUSE FRANKLY,
HER KITCHEN IS BARE.

21:19.930 --> 21:21.018
-OH, WELL GOOD, I'M
OFF IN A FEW MINUTES.

21:21.149 --> 21:22.498
WE'LL GO SHOPPING TOGETHER.

21:22.629 --> 21:23.934
-HONEY, I WANT TO SURPRISE YOU!
[RINGING]

21:24.065 --> 21:25.414
-BUCHANNON.

21:25.545 --> 21:27.024
-I'M QUITE SURPRISED
ALREADY ACTUALLY,

21:27.155 --> 21:28.330
I DON'T NOW IF
I CAN TAKE ANY MORE

21:28.461 --> 21:29.375
OF YOUR SURPRISES, MOM.

21:29.505 --> 21:30.680
[LAUGHS]

21:30.811 --> 21:32.203
-YEAH, HANG ON,
SHE'S RIGHT HERE.

21:32.334 --> 21:33.857
SORRY TO INTERRUPT, BUT
THE PHONE'S FOR YOU.

21:36.469 --> 21:39.210
-FOR ME?
WHO WOULD KNOW I WAS HERE?

21:39.341 --> 21:40.603
-THAT'S A GOOD QUESTION.

21:40.734 --> 21:41.735
-UH, WHO'S CALLING?

21:42.692 --> 21:43.780
TONY BLANTON.

21:43.911 --> 21:46.043
[QUIRKY MUSIC]

21:48.959 --> 21:49.917
-OH.

21:53.355 --> 21:55.009
HELLO? HELLO?

21:55.139 --> 21:56.793
NO, I CAN'T HEAR YOU!

21:56.924 --> 21:58.317
I'M SORRY, YOU HAVE
THE WRONG NUMBER.

21:58.447 --> 21:59.230
-NOW WAIT A SECOND,
WHO'S TONY BLANTON?

22:00.754 --> 22:02.146
-I DON'T KNOW, NOBODY.

22:02.277 --> 22:03.713
-NOW, WAIT A SECOND,
THAT IS THE SECOND TIME

22:03.844 --> 22:04.801
YOU'VE HAD A CONVERSATION
WITH NOBODY TODAY.

22:04.932 --> 22:06.368
YOU'RE NOT GOING ANYWHERE.

22:06.934 --> 22:08.762
MITCH, CAN I HAVE A FEW
MINUTES WITH MY MOM, PLEASE?

22:08.892 --> 22:09.937
WE NEED TO HAVE A LITTLE TALK.

22:10.067 --> 22:11.460
-ABSOLUTELY! FAR BE IT FROM ME

22:11.591 --> 22:12.809
TO INTERRUPT
A MOTHER-DAUGHTER CHAT.

22:15.769 --> 22:17.161
-ALL RIGHT, CAN YOU
HAVE A SEAT PLEASE

22:17.292 --> 22:18.772
BECAUSE YOU'RE GOING
TO SPILL YOUR GUTS.

22:21.165 --> 22:22.123
-OKAY.

22:26.083 --> 22:27.041
[SIGHS]

22:27.171 --> 22:27.998
-GIVE.

22:28.521 --> 22:30.000
-IT'S NOTHING, REALLY.

22:30.131 --> 22:31.393
-I KNOW YOU, MOM.

22:31.524 --> 22:34.048
"NOTHING" ALWAYS
MEANS "SOMETHING".

22:34.918 --> 22:36.659
NOW, COME ON, I KNOW
YOU'RE IN TROUBLE.

22:37.486 --> 22:39.314
BUT I CAN'T HELP YOU
UNLESS YOU TRUST ME.

22:41.795 --> 22:42.665
-WELL...

22:44.580 --> 22:46.756
I GOT INVOLVED WITH MR. WRONG.

22:47.366 --> 22:49.063
-AGAIN?
-AGAIN.

22:49.193 --> 22:51.370
I MEAN, WHAT CAN
I SAY? IT'S A GIFT.

22:52.458 --> 22:54.547
-IT'S A CURSE.
-YEAH.

22:54.677 --> 22:55.983
-I NEED TO MEET THESE MEN

22:56.113 --> 22:57.114
BEFORE YOU GET
SO INVOLVED WITH THEM.

22:57.245 --> 22:58.725
THAT WAY I CAN CHECK THEM OUT.

22:58.855 --> 23:00.509
THEN THEY CAN'T
BREAK YOUR HEART.

23:01.031 --> 23:02.381
-OR MY LEGS! [LAUGHS]

23:03.991 --> 23:05.122
-WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

23:05.732 --> 23:06.994
-WELL...

23:07.516 --> 23:09.300
-JUST START FROM THE BEGINNING,
GIVE ME ALL THE DETAILS.

23:11.738 --> 23:12.782
-OKAY.

23:13.304 --> 23:15.263
SHOULD I GIVE YOU THE
READER'S DIGEST VERSION?

23:15.394 --> 23:18.179
-ALL OF IT, OR I'M
GOING TO BREAK YOUR LEGS.

23:18.309 --> 23:22.966
[LANGUID MUSIC]

23:26.274 --> 23:28.494
MOM, I CAN'T BELIEVE YOU GET
YOURSELF IN THESE SITUATIONS.

23:28.624 --> 23:30.147
-WELL, HOW DID I KNOW
HE WAS GOING TO BE

23:30.278 --> 23:32.367
DUMPING THESE GIRLFRIENDS
GOD KNOWS WHERE

23:32.498 --> 23:34.151
WHEN THEIR GOOD LUCK WORE OFF?

23:34.674 --> 23:36.676
THERE HE IS!
-CJ: WHICH ONE?

23:36.806 --> 23:38.808
-THAT ONE, RIGHT THERE,
HE'S GETTING OUT OF THE POOL.

23:38.939 --> 23:40.723
[LAUGHS]

23:40.854 --> 23:42.769
-HERE YOU GO, MR. BLANTON.
-YEAH, THANKS. THANKS, VINNIE.

23:43.378 --> 23:44.727
-HE'S GOT "MOB"
WRITTEN ALL OVER HIM.

23:44.858 --> 23:46.903
-HA! YEAH, THAT'S
VINNIE WITH HIM.

23:47.034 --> 23:48.731
-VINNIE? FIGURES.

23:49.340 --> 23:51.299
-WAIT, WAIT!

23:54.389 --> 23:55.956
CJ, CJ!

23:58.915 --> 24:00.830
-TWO GRAND MARNIERS
AND MARGARITAS.

24:01.352 --> 24:02.658
-WAITRESS: UH-HUH, ALL RIGHT.

24:05.574 --> 24:08.229
-NOW, LISTEN TO ME, YOU GOON!

24:08.359 --> 24:09.839
I WANT YOU TO STAY
AWAY FROM MY MOM.

24:09.970 --> 24:11.362
-YEAH, AND QUIT FOLLOWING ME

24:11.493 --> 24:13.452
AND SENDING VINNIE
TO THREATEN ME!

24:13.582 --> 24:16.063
AND BOTH OF YOU, DON'T
GO NEAR MY DAUGHTER.

24:16.193 --> 24:19.719
-OH, SO THIS IS
YOUR DAUGHTER, HUH?

24:19.849 --> 24:22.591
ELKIE, I'LL MEET YOU RIGHT
HERE IN A LITTLE WHILE.

24:23.505 --> 24:25.768
IT IS A GREAT
PLEASURE TO MEET YOU.

24:25.899 --> 24:27.727
-WELL, IT'S DEFINITELY NOT
A PLEASURE TO MEET YOU.

24:27.857 --> 24:29.859
[LAUGHS]

24:29.990 --> 24:32.558
-FIRE IN THE DAUGHTER JUST
LIKE THE MOTHER, I LOVE IT.

24:32.688 --> 24:33.384
[LAUGHS]

24:34.821 --> 24:35.996
AND YOU SHOULDN'T HAVE LEFT

24:36.126 --> 24:38.651
WITHOUT SAYING
GOODBYE, BABY DOLL!

24:38.781 --> 24:41.958
-LEFT? I CAN'T EVEN BELIEVE
THAT I EVER STARTED WITH YOU!

24:42.089 --> 24:44.308
I KNOW WHAT YOU'RE CAPABLE OF,

24:44.439 --> 24:46.833
AND I DON'T INTEND TO
END UP LIKE THE OTHERS.

24:46.963 --> 24:48.530
-WHAT OTHERS?

24:48.661 --> 24:50.489
-THE OTHERS, THE OTHER WOMEN

24:50.619 --> 24:52.099
WHO WERE YOUR GOOD LUCK CHARMS?

24:52.752 --> 24:53.753
THEY DISAPPEARED?

24:53.883 --> 24:55.276
[LAUGHS]

24:56.277 --> 24:59.323
-WHERE DOES SHE GET THESE
PREPOSTEROUS STORIES?

24:59.454 --> 25:01.978
I AM HERE BECAUSE
YOU GOT MY DISK.

25:02.109 --> 25:05.634
-OH, YEAH? WELL, I DECIDED TO
TAKE OUT A LITTLE INSURANCE.

25:05.765 --> 25:10.073
THE IRS WOULD BE PARTICULARLY
INTERESTED IN THE WINS,

25:10.204 --> 25:11.945
ALL THE UNREPORTED WINS.

25:12.075 --> 25:15.165
WE FIGURE ABOUT
A COUPLE OF MILLION BUCKS

25:15.296 --> 25:16.993
YOU OWE IN BACK TAXES.

25:17.124 --> 25:19.953
-AND IF MOM AND I
STAY HEALTHY AND ALIVE,

25:20.083 --> 25:21.607
THE IRS DOESN'T
HAVE TO FIND OUT.

25:21.737 --> 25:25.872
-YOU TWO BROADS, YOU WATCH
FAR TOO MUCH TELEVISION!

25:26.002 --> 25:28.004
-WELL, OBVIOUSLY YOU
HAVEN'T BEEN WATCHING ENOUGH

25:28.135 --> 25:29.136
BECAUSE IF YOU DID, YOU'D KNOW

25:29.266 --> 25:30.529
WHAT WAS GOING TO HAPPEN NEXT.

25:32.748 --> 25:34.968
NOW DON'T MESS WITH MY MOM!

25:35.098 --> 25:36.099
BELIEVE ME.

25:36.839 --> 25:38.624
I'VE HAD PLENTY
OF YEARS OF EXPERIENCE

25:38.754 --> 25:39.842
AND YOU WON'T WIN.

25:39.973 --> 25:41.670
-YEAH!
-CJ: YEAH!

25:44.412 --> 25:46.196
-TONY DOESN'T
LOOK SO TOUGH NOW!

25:46.327 --> 25:47.502
-I THINK HE GOT THE MESSAGE.

25:47.633 --> 25:49.112
-YEAH, NEITHER DOES
BIG OLD VINNIE!

25:49.243 --> 25:50.244
-CJ: MM!

25:51.767 --> 25:54.814
-THE WOMAN GIVES NEW MEANING
TO THE PHRASE "BAD LUCK".

25:55.728 --> 25:57.425
-SHE SEEMS TO KNOW
ABOUT THE OTHERS.

25:58.513 --> 26:00.341
-YEAH, NOW THE DAUGHTER
KNOWS EVERYTHING.

26:00.471 --> 26:01.864
THEY KNOW FAR TOO MUCH.

26:02.473 --> 26:04.214
YOU GOT TO FIND THE DISK FOR ME,

26:04.345 --> 26:05.912
AND THEN I WANT YOU TO TAKE CARE

26:06.042 --> 26:07.435
OF SHELLEY AND HER DAUGHTER.

26:07.566 --> 26:09.524
MAKE IT LOOK LIKE AN
ACCIDENT, ALL RIGHT?

26:09.655 --> 26:13.049
-DON'T WORRY, MR. BLANTON,
I'LL TAKE CARE OF IT.

26:13.180 --> 26:14.050
-GOOD.
[OMINOUS MUSIC]

26:14.790 --> 26:16.662
LOOK AT THIS MESS.

26:17.576 --> 26:18.838
[SWING MUSIC]

26:18.968 --> 26:20.230
-NOW WE'RE SHAKING
OUR SHOULDERS.

26:20.361 --> 26:21.580
OKAY, ARE YOU READY?

26:21.710 --> 26:25.801
NOW, ONE, TWO, THREE, FOUR.

26:25.932 --> 26:28.891
ONE MORE, ONE MORE,
NOW WE TWIRL!

26:29.022 --> 26:30.414
TWIRL, ONE MORE TIME.

26:30.545 --> 26:31.894
[LAUGHS]

26:32.025 --> 26:35.245
NOW YOU THRUSH AND YOU THRUSH.

26:35.376 --> 26:37.073
HA!

26:37.204 --> 26:38.248
THIS IS THE PART WHERE THE
FELLAS THREW ME IN THE AIR,

26:38.379 --> 26:39.554
I LOVE THAT PART.

26:39.685 --> 26:41.600
[LAUGHTER]
[CLAPPING]

26:41.730 --> 26:42.992
COME ON.
-BRAVO!

26:43.123 --> 26:43.906
-BOTH OF YOU, COME ON.
-NO, NO, NO, NO.

26:44.037 --> 26:45.299
-COME ON, LET'S TRY IT.

26:45.429 --> 26:46.387
-MOM, THEY'RE
TIRED, THEY'RE TIRED

26:46.517 --> 26:47.649
FROM LIFEGUARDING ALL DAY, MOM.

26:47.780 --> 26:49.216
-OH, NO, YOU'RE
NOT TIRED ARE YOU?

26:49.346 --> 26:50.739
-NO, THIS IS THE QUIET
PART OF THE EVENING,

26:50.870 --> 26:51.827
YOU KNOW, WHERE YOU LAY
BACK AND HANG AND RELAX?

26:51.958 --> 26:53.046
-NO, NO, NO, COME ON. COME ON!

26:53.176 --> 26:54.569
COME ON, YOU GO OVER THERE.

26:54.700 --> 26:55.657
-CJ!

26:55.788 --> 26:57.441
[GROANS]
-GO! GET READY.

26:57.572 --> 26:58.791
OKAY, COME ON.
[SWING MUSIC]

26:58.921 --> 27:00.531
GET THE BEAT. SHAKE
YOUR SHOULDERS.

27:00.662 --> 27:02.011
COME ON, YEAH.

27:02.142 --> 27:03.404
GET READY!

27:03.534 --> 27:07.016
ONE, TWO, TO THE RIGHT,
TO THE LEFT,

27:07.147 --> 27:08.365
ONE MORE TIME!

27:08.496 --> 27:10.106
OKAY, YOU GOT IT!

27:10.237 --> 27:12.456
NOW TWIRL EVERYBODY, TWIRL!

27:12.587 --> 27:14.154
[LAUGHS]

27:14.284 --> 27:17.940
OKAY, NOW THRUSH, AND A THRUSH.

27:18.071 --> 27:20.116
NOW THIS IS THE PART
WHERE WE GO IN THE AIR!

27:20.247 --> 27:22.205
[LAUGHTER]

27:22.336 --> 27:23.685
I LOVE THIS PART!

27:24.381 --> 27:26.035
-I THINK I'LL STICK
TO TAN AND SURFING.

27:27.210 --> 27:29.604
-NO, YOU'D BE A GOOD LIFTER!

27:30.692 --> 27:32.433
COME ON, I'LL GIVE
YOU A GLASS OF WINE.

27:32.563 --> 27:34.087
-THANKS.
-YOU DID GOOD!

27:34.827 --> 27:37.003
-YOUR MOM IS NUTS,
JUST LIKE YOU, CJ.

27:37.133 --> 27:38.178
-[LAUGHS] I KNOW.

27:39.919 --> 27:40.876
TA-DAA!

27:49.015 --> 27:49.885
-HONEY.

27:51.234 --> 27:54.281
I WANT TO THANK YOU AGAIN
FOR HELPING ME OUT TODAY.

27:55.282 --> 27:56.675
I HATED INVOLVING YOU,

27:56.805 --> 27:59.155
BUT I DIDN'T WANT
TO LIE TO YOU EITHER.

27:59.286 --> 28:01.070
-WELL, I JUST HOPE YOU
LEARNED YOUR LESSON

28:01.201 --> 28:03.333
ABOUT GETTING INVOLVED WITH
THE WRONG TYPE OF PEOPLE.

28:04.595 --> 28:06.423
I STILL THINK YOU
SHOULD CALL THE POLICE.

28:07.033 --> 28:08.556
-WELL, WHAT CAN THEY DO?

28:08.687 --> 28:11.211
BECAUSE TONY,
ALL HE DID WAS THREATEN ME.

28:11.777 --> 28:13.648
I KNOW HOW TO HANDLE HIM.

28:13.779 --> 28:16.390
MONEY AND GAMBLING,
THAT IS THE ONLY THING

28:16.520 --> 28:18.218
THAT'S IMPORTANT TO HIM.

28:18.348 --> 28:21.569
AS LONG AS I HAVE THE DISK,
THEN WE'LL BE FINE.

28:21.700 --> 28:23.310
-SPEAKING OF THE
DISK, WHERE IS IT?

28:23.440 --> 28:25.486
-UH, DISK? WHAT DISK?

28:25.616 --> 28:26.487
HERE YOU GO.

28:27.444 --> 28:30.230
-NOT DISK, DISCO!

28:30.360 --> 28:32.014
-DISCO!
-[LAUGHS] COME ON.

28:32.145 --> 28:34.147
-OH, NO! [LAUGHS]

28:38.542 --> 28:43.156
[PEACEFUL MUSIC]

28:48.161 --> 28:49.597
-CASEY JEAN, I'VE HAD THE MOST

28:49.728 --> 28:52.339
FABULOUSLY PEACEFUL DAY TODAY.

28:52.469 --> 28:53.644
REALLY!

28:53.775 --> 28:55.211
I FEEL LIKE A BIG
WEIGHT HAS BEEN

28:55.342 --> 28:57.170
LIFTED OFF MY SHOULDERS.
I HATE TO LEAVE.

29:00.956 --> 29:02.436
-WELL, I'M FINISHED CLOSING UP.

29:03.306 --> 29:04.394
-SHELLEY: OKAY.

29:10.487 --> 29:11.532
-ALL RIGHT, LET'S GO!

29:12.185 --> 29:14.535
-DID YOU SEE THIS GUY?
HUH? LOOK.

29:14.665 --> 29:16.798
THINK HE LIKES OLDER
WOMEN? [LAUGHS]

29:18.408 --> 29:19.453
-GOOD?
-YEAH.

29:23.022 --> 29:24.588
OH, I LOVE THIS PLACE.

29:24.719 --> 29:26.329
I SHOULD HAVE GOT A JOB
LIKE THIS WHEN I WAS A KID!

29:31.334 --> 29:32.422
OH, THIS BAG...

29:32.553 --> 29:33.467
[OMINOUS MUSIC]

29:33.597 --> 29:35.251
-UH-OH, MOM, WE GOT TO GO.

29:35.382 --> 29:37.819
BACKUP, I'M CALLING FOR BACKUP!

29:41.127 --> 29:42.345
-CASEY JEAN, LET'S GO!

29:42.476 --> 29:43.738
[SCREAMING]

29:52.138 --> 29:54.227
WHERE, WHERE, WHERE, WHERE?

29:57.186 --> 29:58.709
[SCREAMING]

29:58.840 --> 30:02.235
-MOM!
-[GRUNTING] CJ!

30:02.365 --> 30:04.933
[MOANING]

30:07.675 --> 30:09.808
VINNIE, YOU'VE GOT TO HELP ME!

30:10.591 --> 30:13.507
[GROANING]

30:18.642 --> 30:20.862
-MOM, ARE YOU OKAY?
-FINE.

30:20.993 --> 30:23.604
-LADIES, THE HONOR OF YOUR
PRESENCE HAS BEEN REQUESTED.

30:24.474 --> 30:25.345
-OW!

30:26.781 --> 30:27.695
OW!

30:28.522 --> 30:30.567
WHO'S THAT GUY, THE
NEW GOON OF THE MONTH?

30:30.698 --> 30:32.308
OW!

30:35.877 --> 30:37.400
WHERE ARE YOU TAKING US?

30:37.531 --> 30:38.532
WAIT!

30:40.055 --> 30:41.013
-WAIT!

30:43.929 --> 30:45.495
-LET'S JUST BE A LITTLE
MORE GENTLE, OKAY?

30:47.715 --> 30:49.717
YOU USED TO BE SUCH
A NICE GUY, VINNIE.

30:57.246 --> 31:00.597
-LADIES, WHAT A NICE SURPRISE.

31:00.728 --> 31:02.469
HAVE A SEAT, PLEASE, WON'T YOU?

31:03.252 --> 31:07.648
AW, COME ON, GIRLS. PLEASE?

31:10.259 --> 31:11.695
[GASPS]

31:11.826 --> 31:14.481
NOW LADIES, THIS ISN'T
USUALLY MY STYLE.

31:14.611 --> 31:17.136
I DON'T ORDINARILY DO COVES.

31:17.266 --> 31:19.442
BUT I DECIDED TO
MAKE AN EXCEPTION.

31:19.573 --> 31:21.444
CAN I OFFER YOU
SOME CHAMPAGNE?

31:21.575 --> 31:22.619
[SCOFFS]

31:23.707 --> 31:24.578
NO?

31:25.709 --> 31:27.624
IT'S REALLY VERY SIMPLE.

31:27.755 --> 31:30.018
THE WAY I SEE IT,
YOU GOT TWO CHOICES.

31:30.149 --> 31:32.194
YOU CAN GIVE ME THE
DISK AND WALK AWAY,

31:32.325 --> 31:35.415
OR YOU CAN SAY GOODBYE
TO EACH OTHER RIGHT NOW.

31:35.545 --> 31:37.156
SO WHAT'S IT GOING TO BE?

31:37.286 --> 31:38.679
-I TOLD YOU THAT
IF ANYTHING HAPPENED

31:38.809 --> 31:40.986
TO EITHER ONE OF US,
THE DISK IS GOING TO BE

31:41.116 --> 31:44.250
IN THE HANDS OF THE
IRS, AND I MADE COPIES!

31:46.948 --> 31:48.341
-I'M A GAMBLING MAN, YOU KNOW?

31:49.603 --> 31:52.301
I SPENT MY WHOLE LIFE
KNOWING WHEN TO GAMBLE,

31:52.432 --> 31:53.868
AND WHEN NOT TO.

31:54.825 --> 31:56.392
I KNOW A BLUFF
WHEN I SEE ONE.

31:58.351 --> 32:01.571
MY INSTINCTS TELL ME THAT
YOU'RE BLUFFING, BABY DOLL.

32:01.702 --> 32:04.661
-TONY, YOU'RE
ON A LOSING STREAK

32:04.792 --> 32:06.533
AND YOU'RE GOING TO LOSE AGAIN.

32:06.663 --> 32:09.449
-LET ME REPHRASE
MY GENEROUS OFFER.

32:09.579 --> 32:12.278
YESTERDAY, YOU ALMOST SAW

32:12.408 --> 32:14.497
SOMEBODY'S CHILD
DROWN ON THE BEACH.

32:15.237 --> 32:18.240
HOW WOULD YOU LIKE TO
SEE YOUR CHILD DROWN, EH?

32:19.938 --> 32:22.027
OH, THE OCEAN IS RIGHT THERE,

32:22.157 --> 32:24.812
AND VINNIE AND GABE
ARE STANDING THERE.

32:26.988 --> 32:28.816
HOW DO YOU THINK
SHE'D LIKE TO WATCH

32:28.947 --> 32:30.122
HER LIFEGUARD DROWN?

32:30.252 --> 32:31.514
[LAUGHTER]

32:31.645 --> 32:32.907
-OH, YOU'RE NOT
SERIOUS, YOU CAN'T BE!

32:33.038 --> 32:34.561
[SCREAMING]
HEY, STOP THAT!

32:34.691 --> 32:37.303
NOW, ALL RIGHT, I'LL GET IT
FOR YOU, I HID IT.

32:37.433 --> 32:39.653
I PUT IT IN CJ'S
LOCKER AT HEADQUARTERS.

32:39.783 --> 32:41.002
NOW, CAN WE GO?

32:41.133 --> 32:43.004
-YOUR LOVELY
DAUGHTER CAN GO NOW,

32:43.135 --> 32:46.094
AND GET THE DISK FOR US.

32:46.225 --> 32:47.835
-HOW DO WE KNOW THAT
YOU WON'T KILL US ANYWAY?

32:47.966 --> 32:50.098
-YOU DON'T KNOW.

32:50.229 --> 32:53.058
BUT HEY, YOU GOT TO TAKE
THAT CHANCE, THAT GAMBLE.

32:53.188 --> 32:54.929
BECAUSE YOU GOT NO OTHER CHOICE.

32:56.583 --> 32:57.932
NOW,

32:58.063 --> 33:00.456
YOU BE BACK IN ONE
HOUR, YOU HEAR ME?

33:00.587 --> 33:04.156
ONE HOUR OR YOUR MOM IS GOING
TO GO FOR A LITTLE SWIM.

33:07.072 --> 33:08.073
HEY!

33:09.291 --> 33:11.119
I WANT YOU TO COME
BACK BY YOURSELF.

33:12.033 --> 33:13.687
NO COPS.

33:13.817 --> 33:16.385
-AND YOU ACCUSE US OF
WATCHING TOO MUCH TELEVISION.

33:16.516 --> 33:17.430
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK, MOM.

33:17.560 --> 33:21.390
[QUIRKY MUSIC]

33:30.486 --> 33:32.836
-WELL, AS LONG WE'RE GOING
TO WAIT, CAN I HAVE A DRINK?

33:32.967 --> 33:35.622
-OH, SURE, BY ALL MEANS.

33:38.581 --> 33:40.409
IT'S GOOD STUFF, VERY GOOD YEAR.

33:41.497 --> 33:44.370
WHOA! GOOD LUCK. [LAUGHS]

33:44.500 --> 33:46.285
HERE YOU ARE, SWEETHEART.

33:48.548 --> 33:49.549
HEY, SALUD!

33:52.030 --> 33:53.118
-UP YOURS, VINNIE.

33:53.901 --> 33:56.121
-AW, COME ON, WE'RE
GOING TO BE FRIENDS,

33:56.251 --> 33:59.689
AREN'T WE, BABY DOLL? [LAUGHS]

33:59.820 --> 34:03.432
-SO THE VICTIM'S
NAME WAS WALT, 14...

34:03.563 --> 34:05.695
HEY, CJ, HOW WAS YOUR DAY?

34:15.574 --> 34:16.924
-DISK, DISK, DISK, DISK.

34:19.534 --> 34:20.580
-WHAT'S WRONG?

34:20.710 --> 34:23.235
-NOTHING! NOTHING. UM...

34:23.364 --> 34:26.150
-CJ, I KNOW SOMETHING IS WRONG.

34:26.281 --> 34:28.978
-NO, NO, I JUST HAVE
TO GET OUT OF HERE.

34:31.460 --> 34:32.896
BYE.

34:45.474 --> 34:48.172
HERE! NOW, COME ON, MOM,
LET'S GO.

34:48.303 --> 34:48.998
-NOT SO FAST!

34:49.609 --> 34:51.045
VINNIE, I WANT YOU
TO CHECK AROUND,

34:51.176 --> 34:52.090
MAKE SURE SHE DIDN'T
BRING BACK ANYONE.

34:53.656 --> 34:56.050
-DID YOU BRING SOMEBODY?

34:56.181 --> 34:56.964
-WHAT?

35:12.110 --> 35:13.502
-EVERYTHING'S
COOL, MR. BLANTON.

35:13.633 --> 35:15.200
THERE'S NOBODY OUT THERE.

35:16.288 --> 35:17.854
-THIS IS THE CORRECT DISK.

35:17.985 --> 35:19.334
-GOOD, THEN WE CAN GO.

35:19.465 --> 35:21.162
-NOT SO FAST.

35:21.293 --> 35:23.121
SORRY, BUT THAT I CANNOT ALLOW.

35:23.251 --> 35:26.254
-I KNEW YOU WERE GOING
TO DO THIS, YOU BIG JERK!

35:26.385 --> 35:28.517
-YOU SAID IF I BROUGHT YOU
THE DISK THAT WE COULD GO!

35:28.648 --> 35:29.605
-I LIED.

35:32.434 --> 35:34.219
COME ON, LET'S GET
GOING. OVER HERE.

35:42.618 --> 35:46.579
[TENSE MUSIC]

35:49.756 --> 35:50.713
-CJ: GEEZ!

35:51.714 --> 35:53.629
-SHELLEY: OW!

35:53.760 --> 35:54.804
OW!

35:55.892 --> 36:00.549
[SHOUTING]

36:00.680 --> 36:04.292
[INTENSE MUSIC]

36:04.423 --> 36:08.557
[GRUNTING]

36:18.045 --> 36:21.179
[SHOUTING]

36:31.667 --> 36:33.060
-GET OVER THERE,
GET OVER THERE!

36:36.498 --> 36:37.760
-CJ: GET HIM, MOM!

36:37.891 --> 36:38.631
-YOU SHOULD LIFT
SOME MORE WEIGHT!

36:39.371 --> 36:41.764
[GRUNTING]

36:43.984 --> 36:44.985
-GIVE UP?

36:45.594 --> 36:46.508
-MITCH: GET UP!

36:51.470 --> 36:52.645
-KICK HIM, HONEY, KICK HIM!

36:52.775 --> 36:55.082
KICK HIM, KICK HIM!

36:55.213 --> 36:56.605
YEAH!

36:56.736 --> 36:57.258
-CODY: THAT'S FOR MY
GIRLFRIEND'S MOTHER!

36:58.868 --> 36:59.913
-CJ: GET HIM, MOM!

37:02.045 --> 37:06.615
[SHOUTING]

37:10.097 --> 37:11.490
-COME ON, COME ON!

37:12.360 --> 37:13.231
LET'S GO.

37:14.101 --> 37:17.757
[SHOUTING]

37:17.887 --> 37:19.411
-YOUR CRIMES ARE
OVER, YOUNG MAN.

37:26.809 --> 37:27.854
-CODY: LET'S GO, MOVE IT.

37:28.681 --> 37:30.291
-COME ON, COME ON, YOU'RE OKAY.

37:30.422 --> 37:31.423
COME ON OVER HERE. COME ON.

37:31.553 --> 37:32.902
YEAH, YEAH, COME ON, COME ON.

37:33.033 --> 37:37.124
[BICKERING]

37:37.255 --> 37:38.647
-I NEVER THOUGHT I'D
BE THANKING SOMEONE

37:38.778 --> 37:39.822
FOR NOT BELIEVING ME.

37:41.476 --> 37:42.347
[LAUGHS]

37:42.477 --> 37:43.304
-YOU OKAY?
-YEAH.

37:46.699 --> 37:50.268
[PEACEFUL MUSIC]

37:55.751 --> 37:56.752
-HEY, MOM, WHAT YOU THINKING?

37:56.883 --> 37:57.927
-OH.

37:58.450 --> 38:01.540
HOW BEAUTIFUL THE BEACH
IS THIS TIME OF DAY.

38:02.367 --> 38:03.716
HOW PEACEFUL.

38:04.412 --> 38:07.067
AND HOW TONY'S GOING TO
LOOK WEARING THOSE STRIPES.

38:07.197 --> 38:09.635
[LAUGHTER]

38:09.765 --> 38:11.419
THIS IS A MAN WHO
WOULD NEVER EVEN

38:11.550 --> 38:13.508
WEAR A STRIPED TIE.

38:14.727 --> 38:17.382
-WELL, SITTING BEHIND BARS IS
EXACTLY WHERE TONY SHOULD BE.

38:17.512 --> 38:18.818
-YEAH.

38:18.948 --> 38:20.036
I TOLD HIM NOT TO
MESS WITH MY MOM,

38:20.167 --> 38:21.211
HE SHOULD HAVE LISTENED.

38:21.342 --> 38:22.778
[LAUGHS]

38:22.909 --> 38:26.042
-CASEY JEAN, I AM SO
HAPPY FOR YOU, HONEY.

38:27.174 --> 38:28.697
YOU HAVE SUCH A GOOD LIFE.

38:30.525 --> 38:33.963
GOT A JOB YOU LOVE AND
OH, SO MANY FRIENDS

38:34.094 --> 38:35.878
WHO REALLY LOVE YOU.

38:38.272 --> 38:40.187
-YEAH, IT'S ALMOST PERFECT.

38:46.715 --> 38:48.630
[MELANCHOLY MUSIC]

38:53.505 --> 38:56.290
-YOU KNOW, WHEN YOU
WERE A LITTLE GIRL

38:56.421 --> 39:00.686
YOU WOULD NEVER, EVER
LET ANYBODY SEE YOU CRY.

39:03.166 --> 39:05.038
NOT EVEN ME.

39:07.388 --> 39:09.521
I GUESS SOME THINGS
NEVER CHANGE, HUH, HONEY?

39:12.219 --> 39:14.003
-I DON'T WANT YOU TO GO, MOM.

39:14.917 --> 39:16.179
-CASEY JEAN,

39:17.050 --> 39:18.965
I NEARLY GOT BOTH OF US KILLED.

39:20.401 --> 39:22.925
I'VE JUST GOT TO GET
MY LIFE TOGETHER NOW.

39:23.622 --> 39:24.797
AND THEN I'M GOING
TO GO OUT THERE

39:24.927 --> 39:26.755
AND SEE WHAT'S LEFT FOR ME.

39:28.409 --> 39:30.803
JUST LIKE YOU DID WHEN
YOU LEFT VEGAS AND ME.

39:32.457 --> 39:33.849
I GOT TO GO NOW.

39:35.895 --> 39:36.765
AND...

39:38.419 --> 39:40.160
I'LL FIND MYSELF

39:41.204 --> 39:43.163
A LITTLE NICHE, YOU KNOW?

39:45.078 --> 39:47.036
-I JUST WISH YOU COULD
FIND YOUR NICHE HERE,

39:47.646 --> 39:48.298
WITH ME.

39:49.778 --> 39:50.605
-WELL,

39:51.780 --> 39:53.695
WHEN I GET THIS ACT TOGETHER

39:53.826 --> 39:55.436
AND I CAN TAKE IT ON THE ROAD,

39:56.829 --> 39:58.308
I'M GOING TO BE BACK.

39:58.439 --> 39:59.484
-REALLY?

40:00.572 --> 40:01.486
PROMISE?

40:01.616 --> 40:02.617
-OH.

40:04.358 --> 40:05.533
CASEY JEAN.

40:08.841 --> 40:10.712
ALL THE WHILE YOU
WERE GROWING UP

40:10.843 --> 40:13.106
IT WAS JUST YOU

40:13.236 --> 40:15.543
AND ME, REMEMBER?

40:18.241 --> 40:20.635
AND BEING WITH YOU
THESE PAST FEW DAYS

40:20.766 --> 40:22.724
HAS BROUGHT IT ALL
BACK, SWEETHEART.

40:24.334 --> 40:26.206
YOU ARE MY BEST FRIEND.

40:28.513 --> 40:31.385
AND YOU KNOW ME BETTER
THAN ANYBODY, HONEY.

40:33.039 --> 40:35.084
I JUST NEED A LITTLE
TIME NOW AND I'LL...

40:37.130 --> 40:38.261
I'LL BE BACK.

40:41.090 --> 40:42.222
-I LOVE YOU, MOM.

40:42.875 --> 40:44.746
-OH, BABY!

40:46.966 --> 40:48.402
I LOVE YOU.

40:59.805 --> 41:01.328
[LAUGHS]

41:14.472 --> 41:19.128
[CLOSING THEME PLAYING]
